(21, 'Triund Trek Weather', '<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-586b8b\" data-id=\"586b8b\" data-element_type=\"column\">\r\n<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\r\n<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\r\n<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6e43c370 elementor-view-default elementor-mobile-position-top elementor-vertical-align-top elementor-widget elementor-widget-icon-box\" data-id=\"6e43c370\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"icon-box.default\">\r\n<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\r\n<div class=\"elementor-icon-box-wrapper\">\r\n<div class=\"elementor-icon-box-content\">\r\n<h2>Triund Weather</h2>\r\n<p>Triund is a hill station located in the Kangra district, which is located in the Indian state of Himachal Pradesh in India. Triund Hill Station is located in India. Triund Hill Station is a part of Dharamkot. Triund is located at the base of the Dhauladhar range and sits located at an elevation of 2,828 meters. Triund Weather</p>\r\n<p>Triund HillTriund Triund HillTriund is an extensive area of lush green grass and pasture like. It is possible to see the majestic Dhauladhar ranges right above the eye. The ridge\'s elevation ranges between 2,810 and 287 m. It\'s a single-day hike approximately. 10km (one way) from the Mcleod Ganj bus stand and less than 6 km (one direction) of Galu temple in Dharamkot. The path is rough and has steps cut into it in some spots. From the Galu devi temple, there is a straight-forward byway that runs through a stunning woodland of deodar and oak trees. This forest stretch is known as the 22 Curves due to the 22 switchbacks that one has to cross to get to Triund. Triund Weather</p>\r\n<h3>Connectivity and transportation</h3>\r\n<p>The transport by road in the nearby area is Pathankot to Gaggal before heading to Dharamsala as well as New Delhi to the Chandigarh and then on to Kangra and then finally Dharamsala.</p>\r\n<p>The closest stations for railways on the narrow gauge Shimla-Kangra line are in Jassur (Nurpur, Kangra, and Himachal Pradesh) and Paror railway station close to Nagrota (about 20 kilometers to the to the south of Dharamsala). The nearest rail head on broad gauge is located at Pathankot (about 85 kilometers).</p>\r\n<p>Gaggal Airport (which can also be called Kangra Airport) to Gaggal market and then turn left to Dharamsala there is no need to travel to Kangra. Triund Weather</p>\r\n<h3>Triund Campsite</h3>\r\n<p>Triund Campsite is a base camp and an acclimatization point for trekkers who are climbing the Inderahara point on the Mt. Dhauladhar. The night sky view from Triund is an excellent incentive to put up your tent there to sleep. The long distance is ideal to spend a weekend here.</p>\r\n<h3>Climate</h3>\r\n<p>Triund is closed during the months of January and February due to the heavy snowfall. The best time to go trek is between March and May in the beginning of the year and from September until month of December in the second half during the latter half. It\'s rainy during the months of June and July however hiking is feasible. The meadow is lush and green, offering an breathtaking views. The Triund weather</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-586b8b\" data-id=\"586b8b\" data-element_type=\"column\"><div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\"><div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\"><div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6e43c370 elementor-view-default elementor-mobile-position-top elementor-vertical-align-top elementor-widget elementor-widget-icon-box\" data-id=\"6e43c370\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"icon-box.default\"><div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"><div class=\"elementor-icon-box-wrapper\"><div class=\"elementor-icon-box-content\"><ul><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day1</div><h4>Mcleodganj to Triund Hill (4-5 hours of trekking)</h4><p>At 9 AM, you can start your trek from Bhagsu Nag Triund (2875 m).<br>Start your trek from Mcleodganj. You can reach Bhagusu Na and then hike from Bhagsu Nah. It is a magical experience to walk through dense forests of Oak, Rhododendron and deodar. This alpine meadow overlooks the snow-capped peaks at Dhauladhar. The Kangra Valley can be seen from the opposite side. We will then rest for the night after dinner and star gazing at our beautiful mountain lodge.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day2</div><h4>Triund Hill to Snowline and back to Mcleodganj (4-5 hours of trekking)</h4><p>Get up early and see the sunrise over the majestic mountains and Kangra Valley. The finest thing is to be with your own. If you want to visit Snow Line (5Kms), then leave early in the morning from Triund. Else To reach Bhagsu Nag village, it will take approximately 4 to 5 hours. You can also stop at Lahesh cave on the way. Bhagsu Waterfall will be visible. This is the end of your trek.</p></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', '<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-586b8b\" data-id=\"586b8b\" data-element_type=\"column\"><div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\"><div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\"><div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6e43c370 elementor-view-default elementor-mobile-position-top elementor-vertical-align-top elementor-widget elementor-widget-icon-box\" data-id=\"6e43c370\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"icon-box.default\"><div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"><div class=\"elementor-icon-box-wrapper\"><div class=\"elementor-icon-box-content\"><ul><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><p>Cancellations prior to 10 days from the start of the trek are entitled to a full refund(excluding the transaction charges)Cancellation between the 9th day and the 3rd day to the start of the trek will have an 80% refund. Cancellation less than 3 days to the start of the trek will have NO refund. For any assistance mail us at: info@indian-tours.in</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><h4>DISCLAIMER:</h4>This activity is hugely dependent upon weather. The trip may get canceled without any prior notice due to weather or any unforeseen adverse circumstances</div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', NULL, '2', '1', 1000, 1000, 0, 1000, 1000, 0, 1000, 1000, 0, 2000, 2000, 0, 0, '1650013314_small_1648986441_small.jpg', '1650013314_large_triund-camps.jpg', 'Triund Trek Weather', 'Triund Trek Weather', 'publish', '1650013314_banner.jpg', 'Triund Trek Weather', 'Dharmshala Triund', 'Triund Trek Weather', 'triund-weather', '2022-04-15 13:01:54', '2022-04-25 13:14:34'),
