(42, 'Chandratal Lake Trek With Hampta Pass', '<p><span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"7\">Hampta Pass Trek with Chandratal could be a passageway that connects the Lahaul\'s Chandra valley, and Kullu valley.</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"4\">As it is a passageway between two vibrant valleys, Hampta pass gives us the chance to see.</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"9\">When you travel through your way through the Pir Panjal ranges on this hike, you\'ll be able to see several shepherds who are grazing their flocks in the grasslands.</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"2\">Also popular are the Manali Treks in Himachal and India.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"1\">Himachal Pradesh is one of the states with the highest number of tourists in India.</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"5\">The state is blessed with beautiful, stunning snow-covered mountains, which provide a significant tourist draw.</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"10\">Trekkers and tourists from across the globe come to this stunning, unpolluted and tranquil location to nourish their mind and souls and appreciate the unimaginable beauty of nature.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"10\">Height - 14,100 feet</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"10\">Hampta Pass&nbsp; Altitude - 4270 meters above sea level</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"10\">Chandratal lake Altitude - 4300 meters above sea level</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"10\">The trek to Hampta Pass Trek With Chandratal could be an passageway between the Lahaul\'s Chandra valley, and Kullu valley. It is a bridge between two vibrant valleys, Hampta pass gives us an amazing view.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"10\">When you trek through in the Pir Panjal ranges during the trek you\'ll be able to see many shepherds tending their sheep in the grasslands. Manali Treks are also famous in Himachal and India.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"wordai-block rewrite-block enable-highlight\" data-id=\"10\">- How do I get to the point of departure for treks.</span></p>\r\n<p>The closest Hub to where trek start is Manali. The journey therefore begins at Manali and continues to Chika through Jobra. After Jobra it is done on foot, and this trek includes the first day.</p>\r\n<p>Best Season To visit Chandratal Lake Trek With Hampta Pass</p>\r\n<p>The most enjoyable months to hike are June and May and August to October.</p>\r\n<p>The reason Trek To Hampta Pass is one of the most popular trekking zones is the snow. The pass is covered with an accumulation of snow that attracts many tourists. Chandratal Lake Trek with Hampta Pass Difficulty Level.</p>\r\n<p>Hampta Pass Trek with Chandratal is a Moderate level.</p>', '<ul><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day1</div><h4>Manali</h4><p>Check-in Time : 9:30 A.M All trekkers will meet in Manali</p><p>- Accommodation In Manali<br>- Evening Snacks,Dinner,Bonfire</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day2</div><h4>Travel starting from Manali to Jobri Vilage (2hrs) To Chikka (4hrs)</h4><p>Start Time: 9:30 A.M</p><p>The adventure begins with the tranquil and captivating jeep ride across the Jobra from base camp. Jobra. The hike will take a reasonable amount of time to reach the destination . in the words of the saying, more than the destination is more important, and this is where the trek is important to consider the following: The relaxing and peaceful journey that lasts for about two hours.</p><p>-Breakfast, Packed Lunch, Evening Snacks, Dinner<br>-Camps - Camps<br>-Guide &amp; Trek Leader &nbsp;</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day3</div><h4>Chikka to Balu Ka Ghera (5 hours)</h4><p>Start Time: 9:30 A.M</p><p>Another day, another wonderful morning as we\'re staying at the gorgeous Chikka camping site. Chikka to Balu Ka ghera (9 K.M) The plan is to walk between Chikka to Balu ka Ghera The trek long and takes 4-5 hours. This could drain your energy. At the beginning, we\'ll cross a few rough river banks. In later parts, the dreamy snow valley is going to lighten our mood and replenish the adrenaline-inducing bar. And camping in Balu ka Ghera no need an introduction, because it\'s an absolute example of beauty.</p><p>-Breakfast,Packed Lunch,Evening Snacks,Dinner<br>-Camps - Camps<br>-Guide &amp; Trek Leader</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day4</div><h4>Balu ka Ghera to Hampta Pass (8hrs) and then up to Shia Ghoru (2hrs)</h4><p>Start Time - 7:30 A.M</p><p>Day 4 is regarded as the most Day of Challaning Day of Trek. Balu ka Ghera to Hampta Pass (8hrs) and on up to Shia Ghoru (2hrs).&nbsp;</p><p>Day 4 starts with a hard-core trek day. Because we will have to go for approximately 8 hours of hiking until the top of the hampta pass. We\'ll try at achieving Shia Ghoru campsite as the trek is expected to last for about 4 to 5 hours before reaching at the Hampta Pass top, from there another few hours will be required to walk toward Shia Ghoru. It\'s a little more steep descend. As we do every day, we\'ll prepare our ourselves to stay the night and settle in the campsite. We\'ll need to refuel and re-energize ourselves for the following day\'s adventure.&nbsp;</p><p>-Breakfast,Packed Lunch,Evening Snacks,Dinner</p><p>-Camps - Camps</p><p>-Guide &amp; Trek Leader</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day5</div><h4>Sia Ghoru Chatru journey until Chandratal (2-hrs-3hrs)</h4><p>Beginning Time - 9:15 A.M</p><p>Sia Ghoru Chatru travel towards Chandratal (9 K.M). The day begins by departing from at the Shia Ghoru camp and walking toward Chatru. The Chatru has stunning and jaw-dropping scenes that can set the mood for your day and your mind in motion. Chatru Chatru is the center of three most stunning locations i.e. Hampta Pass, Rohtang Pass &amp; Spiti valley. In the next part, we\'ll take a good jeep trip to Chadratal. Since Chandratal has historical dipictions and is also a part of the well-known and most acclaimed Mahabharata.</p><p>-Breakfast,Packed Lunch,Evening Snacks,Dinner<br>-Camps - Camps<br>-Guide &amp; Trek Leader<br>-Transportation services between Chatru in Chatru to Chandratal &amp; Back</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day6</div><h4>Jeep Ride from Chatru to Manali Base Camp</h4><p>Start Time: 8:30 A.M</p><p>Jourey back Towards Manali. Jeep Ride starting from Chatru Manali Base Camp to Manali Base Camp. We\'ll leave at 8am from Chatru taking us to our base camp. It\'s an adrenaline rush of adrenaline and panoramic views starting from day one until the final day. Although it\'s the final day nevertheless, we\'ll start our day early. There are a lot of things on the list of things to do for the day\'s schedule. Following the breakfast, we\'ll depart Chatru the first place on the agenda is to reach Manali at noon. We\'ll soon be in Manali. This was an absolute adventure and a pleasure and, with the renowned phrase that says every beginning is an ending and each end is a beginning and we\'ll end our journey on a happy note.</p><p>-Breakfast,<br>-Guide &amp; Trek Leader<br>-Transportation from Chatru to Manali</p></div></li></ul>', '<ul><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><p>Cancellations prior to 10 days from the start of the trek are entitled to a full refund(excluding the transaction charges)Cancellation between the 9th day and the 3rd day to the start of the trek will have an 80% refund. Cancellation less than 3 days to the start of the trek will have NO refund. For any assistance mail us at: info@indian-tours.in</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><h4>DISCLAIMER:</h4>This activity is hugely dependent upon weather. The trip may get canceled without any prior notice due to weather or any unforeseen adverse circumstances</div></li></ul>', '<p>Chandratal Lake Trek With Hampta Pass</p>', '6', '5', 7500, 7500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 15000, 15000, 0, 0, '1653159392_small.jpg', '1653159392_large.jpg', 'Chandratal Lake Trek With Hampta Pass', 'Chandratal Lake Trek With Hampta Pass', 'publish', '1653159392_chandratal-trekking.jpg', 'Chandratal Lake Trek With Hampta Pass', 'Chandratal Lake - Hampta Pass', 'Chandratal Lake Trek With Hampta Pass', 'chandratal-lake-trek', '2022-05-21 21:50:43', '2022-05-22 20:52:11'),
(43, 'Darjeeling, Gangtok & Kalimpong', '<p>Darjeeling, Gangtok &amp; Kalimpong</p>', '<ul><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day1</div><h4><strong>NJP RAILWAY STATION/IXB AIRPORT - DARJEELING :</strong></h4><p>On arrival at NJP Railway Station / IXB Airport, you will be met by our Executive who will assist you to board your vehicle to Darjeeling . Visit mirik Lake &amp; Nepal Border enroute.Overnight at Darjeeling.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day2</div><h4><strong>DARJEELING :</strong></h4><p>After breakfast visit to Padmaja Naidu Himalayan Zoological Park, Himalayan Mountaineering Institute (Closed on Thursday), Tenzing &amp; Gombu. Rock, Tibetan Refugee Self-Help Center (Closed on Sunday),Ropeway, Lebong Race Course &amp; Tea Estate. Afternoon visit to Rock Garden &amp; Ganga Maya Lake. Overnight at Darjeeling.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day3</div><h4><strong>&nbsp;DARJEELING - KALIMPONG :</strong></h4><p>Early morning tour to Tiger Hills (at around 4 am) to view sunrise over KanchenjungaPeak (subject to clear weather). On way back visit Ghoom Monastery, Batasia Loop. After breakfast at hotel, transfer to Kalimpong. Afternoon enjoy a sightseeing of Kalimpong covering Deolo Hill, Dr Graham Homes School, Thonga Goma Monastary, Mangaldham &amp; Nurseries.Overnight at Kalimpong.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day4</div><h4><strong>&nbsp;KALIMPONG - GANGTOK :</strong></h4><p>After breakfast at hote,l transfer to Gangtok. Afternoon enjoy a sightseeing of Gangtok covering Directorate of Handicrafts and Handlooms, Enchey Monastery, Research Institute of Tibetology, Chorten ( Stupa ), Orchid Sanctuary &amp; Rumtek Monastery.Overnight at Gangtok.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day5</div><h4>GANGTOK :</h4><p>This is a day excursion to Tsomgo Lake &amp; Baba Dham (departure in the morning)- situated at a height of 3,780 mts. with an average depth of 50 ft. The cool water of the Lake is perfectly attuned with the scenic beauty around. Return Back to Gangtok. Overnight at Gangtok.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day6</div><h4>GANGTOK - NJP RAILWAY STATION/IXBAIRPORT :</h4><p>After breakfast proceed to NJP Railway Station / IXB Airport for your onward journey.</p></div></li></ul>', '<ul><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><p>Cancellations prior to 10 days from the start of the trek are entitled to a full refund(excluding the transaction charges)Cancellation between the 9th day and the 3rd day to the start of the trek will have an 80% refund. Cancellation less than 3 days to the start of the trek will have NO refund. For any assistance mail us at: info@indian-tours.in</p></div></li></ul>', '<p>Breakfast</p><p>Transportation</p><p>Hotels Stay</p>', '6', '5', 8000, 8000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 16000, 16000, 0, 0, '1653227961_small_gangtok-ropeway.jpg', '1653227961_large_gangtok.jpg', 'Darjeeling, Gangtok & Kalimpong', 'Darjeeling, Gangtok & Kalimpong', 'publish', '1653227961_darjeeling.jpg', 'Darjeeling, Gangtok & Kalimpong', 'Darjeeling - Gangtok - Kalimpong', 'Darjeeling, Gangtok & Kalimpong', 'darjeeling-gangtok-kalimpong', '2022-05-22 17:59:21', '2022-05-22 18:15:49'),
(45, 'Colourful Rajasthan Tour', '<p>Colourful Rajasthan Tour</p>', '<ul><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day1</div><h4><strong>Arrival at Delhi</strong></h4><p>India Gate, Delhi TravelsCompany representatives will receive you on arrival at the DELHI AIRPORT and transfer to your hotel.<br><br>Overnight will be at Delhi.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day2</div><h4><strong>Delhi</strong></h4><p>After breakfast proceed for a half day tour of Old &amp; New Delhi.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day3</div><h4><strong>&nbsp;Delhi - Agra (By Road 221 km/05 hrs)</strong></h4><p>Breakfast will be at hotel.<br><br>Proceed by surface to Agra. Reach and check into the hotel.<br><br>Relax in the evening. Overnight will be at Agra.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day4</div><h4><strong>Agra - Jaipur (By Road 221 km/05 hrs)</strong></h4><p>Taj Mahal, Agra TourismAfter breakfast drive to beautiful Pink City - Jaipur.<br><br>Reach and check in at hotel.<br><br>Overnight will be at Jaipur</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day5</div><h4><strong>Jaipur</strong></h4><p>After breakfast drive to Amber Palace. Enjoy Elephant Back ascent to the Fort.<br><br>Continue city sightseeing.<br><br>Shopping in the evening or relax. Overnight will be at Jaipur.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day6</div><h4><strong>Jaipur - Jodhpur (By Road 280 km/06 hrs)</strong></h4><p>Breakfast will be at hotel. Proceed to Jodhpur. Reach Jodhpur and check into hotel.<br><br>Overnight will be at Jodhpur.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day7</div><h4><strong>Jodhpur - Udaipur (By Road 250km/05hrs)</strong></h4><p>Jodhpur Fort, Jodhpur TravelsBreakfast will be at hotel. Proceed to Udaipur.<br><br>Overnight will be at Udaipur.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day8</div><h4><strong>Udaipur</strong></h4><p>Breakfast will be at hotel.<br><br>Relax in the evening. Overnight will be at Udaipur.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day9</div><h4><strong>Udaipur - Pushkar (By Road 250km/05hrs)</strong></h4><p>Proceed for Pushkar after breakfast.<br><br>Visit the DARGAH. Reach Pushkar by noon and relax. Check in at PUSHKAR PALACE.<br><br>Overnight at PUSHKAR.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day10</div><h4><strong>Pushkar - Kishangrah - Delhi (By Road 352km/07 hrs)</strong></h4><p>Pushkar Fair, Pushkar ravels &amp; ToursDrive to Kishangarh after breakfast.</p><p>Lunch will be at PHOOL MAHAL PALACE.</p><p>Start for Delhi and reach by evening. Transfer for connecting flight home from the international airport.</p></div></li></ul>', '<p>Cancellations prior to 10 days from the start of the trek are entitled to a full refund(excluding the transaction charges)Cancellation between the 9th day and the 3rd day to the start of the trek will have an 80% refund. Cancellation less than 3 days to the start of the trek will have NO refund. For any assistance mail us at: info@indian-tours.in</p>', '<p>Breakfast</p><p>Transportation</p><p>Stay</p>', '10', '9', 18000, 18000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 36000, 36000, 0, 0, '1653230109_small_hanuman-ji-temple-jaipur-rajasthan-india.jpg', '1653230109_large_rajasthan-india.jpg', 'Colourful Rajasthan Tour', 'Colourful Rajasthan Tour', 'publish', '1653230109_rajasthan.jpg', 'Colourful Rajasthan Tour', 'Delhi - Agra - Jaipur - Jodhpur - Udaipur - Pushkar - Kishangarh - Delhi', 'Colourful Rajasthan Tour', 'colourful-rajasthan-tour', '2022-05-22 18:35:09', '2022-05-22 18:35:09'),
(44, 'Kathmandu & Nagarkot Hilltop Tour', '<p>Kathmandu &amp; Nagarkot Hilltop Tour</p>', '<ul><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day1</div><h4><strong>ARRIVAL IN KATHMANDU.</strong></h4><p>Upon arrival in Kathmandu airport our representative will receive and transfer to hotel in Kathmandu. Rooms will be assigned followed by short briefing about your Tour &amp; over night hotel.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day2</div><h4><strong>KATHMANDU VALLEY TOUR.</strong></h4><p>After breakfast Tour to Swayambunath, National Museum, Patan durbar squire, Pashupatinath Temple and Buddhanath stupa. Both the places are under world heritage site and Budhanilkanth Visnu Temple and overnight hotel.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day3</div><h4><strong>&nbsp;BHAKTAPUR- NAGARKOT</strong></h4><p>After Breakfast, Drive to Bhaktapur durbar Square is a conglomeration of Pagoda and Shikara style temples grouped around a Fifty-five windows palace of brick and woods. The lion gate, golden gate the palace of fifty-five windows. Then proceed onto Changunarayan Temple and continue to NAGARKOT for Sunset tour and overnight hotel</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day4</div><h4><strong>&nbsp;NAGARKOT &ndash; KATHMANDU.</strong></h4><p>Early morning sunrise tour to the nearest vantage point to Himalayan peaks. After breakfast we then proceed onto Kathmandu. Afternoon: Free for shopping and overnight Hotel.</p></div></li><li><div class=\"timeline-content\"><div class=\"day-count\">Day5</div><h4><strong>Kathmandu Final Departure.</strong></h4><p>Mountain Flight over the snow clad Himalaya s including the Everest one will be awarded with a Certificate engraved with individual names. Back to hotel and prepare for final onward journeys.</p></div></li></ul>', '<p>Cancellations prior to 10 days from the start of the trek are entitled to a full refund(excluding the transaction charges)Cancellation between the 9th day and the 3rd day to the start of the trek will have an 80% refund. Cancellation less than 3 days to the start of the trek will have NO refund. For any assistance mail us at: info@indian-tours.in</p>', '<p>Breakfast Dinner</p><p>Stay at Hotel&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '5', '4', 7500, 7500, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 15000, 15000, 0, 0, '1653228910_small_bodhnath-stupa-kathmandu.jpg', '1653228910_large_beautiful-pashupatinath-temple-kathmandunepal.jpg', 'Kathmandu & Nagarkot Hilltop Tour', 'Kathmandu & Nagarkot Hilltop Tour', 'publish', '1653228910_kathmandu.jpg', 'Kathmandu & Nagarkot Hilltop Tour', 'Kathmandu - Nagarkot Hilltop', 'Kathmandu & Nagarkot Hilltop Tour', 'kathmandu-nagarkot-hilltop-tour', '2022-05-22 18:15:10', '2022-05-22 18:15:10');
